data.description: Under contract-accepting backup offers. Welcome to your fabulous new home Nestled in the gorgeous community at Shady Creek. This home is located in the very back of the loop with a 200 foot walk to the preserve or fishing pond.     Your family can actual ride their bikes or walk to school at Creekside Elementary. Talk about a safe neighborhood. Crossing guards and police presence on Highway 301 South for the school traffic.    This stunning and spacious 2007-built home is more than just a place to live – it's a dream come true. With 3 large bedrooms, 2.5 baths, and a roomy 2,968 square feet, it's perfect for anyone who loves a mix of comfort and style. This home features a semi-open floor plan that is perfect for entertaining yourself and many others. You can set up in either of the two living rooms or out on the gorgeous covered lanai.     Step outside to your own private oasis, with ceiling fans for those warm summer evenings, a private heated pool for cool nights, removeable safety fence for the kiddos, and a beautiful built-in fireplace. Imagine the pool parties and chill evenings you can host here or just quiet evenings off of the master access door for a private party after hours. The dog run is complete with doors for their access on either end of the screened pool deck and lanai surrounded by a new vinyl privacy fenced yard.     Love to cook? The kitchen is decked out with all stainless steel Samsung appliances, an oversized island, an industrial kitchen faucet, with a huge sink (making clean-up a breeze) plus, there's a walk-in pantry providing tons of storage for all your favorite foods & even comes with a perfectly oversized sized spice rack. Then there’s the Master Suite Retreat: The master bedroom is your own little sanctuary with direct access to the lanai and pool. It comes with two walk-in closets, a private water closet, and a beautiful stand alone tub – because everyone needs a little "me" time. The wonderful features don’t stop there though.    The Laundry gets an entire room to itself, with shelves, cabinets, more storage space, a front loading Samsung washer & dryer included, and room for a sink should you want one. We've got 2 central air conditioning units and 2 air handlers. A two car finished garage with brick pavers galore all over this property.    This home is nestled in a community that balances the excitement of Florida weather with a safe, cozy vibe. It's the kind of place where you can make lasting memories, host epic BBQs or just kick back and enjoy the good life. Ready to make a move? This home is waiting for you to make it your own!
